text: Anemone coronaria (Spanish marigold) daÄŸ lalesi in Turkish, shaqa'iq An-Nu'man in Arabic is a flowering plant in the genus Anemone. It is native to the Mediterranean region. Anemone coronaria is widely grown for its decorative flowers. Numerous cultivars have been selected and named. == Note == Category:Plants of Asia Category:Ranunculales Category:National symbols of the State of Palestine
title: Anemone coronaria
